	<Title>
		Want to avoid cold sores? Use sunblock
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;No one likes cold sores. These tingling, red lip blisters are tough to hide, and sometimes they&apos;re slow to heal. You can help prevent them by applying sunblock on your lips and face year-round. Avoid kissing anyone who has a cold sore, and don&apos;t share utensils, lip balm, towels or other personal items.&lt;/p&gt;
